name Mulled Wine Torte
serves 1
tags cake, nuts, fruit
related esterhazy-schnitten

# For the sponge

- 50 g dark chocolate
- 60 g butter
Melt and mix.
-> molten chocolate

- 6 eggs
Divide.
-> egg yolk
-> egg whites

- 50 g sugar
= egg whites
Beat until stiff.
-> beaten egg whites

- 50 g sugar
- .5 bean vanilla
= egg yolk
Scrape the vanilla into the egg yolk. Beat with sugar until foamy.
-> foamy egg yolk

- 20 g raisins
- 30 g ground walnuts
- 35 g flour
- 75 g breadcrumb
= molten chocolate
@ foamy egg yolk
@ beaten egg whites
Mix with egg yolk. Carefully mix in egg whites. Bake in a 24cm spring form at 180°C (160°C for convection) for 35 minutes. Let cool.
-> sponge


# For the filling

- 3 "untreated oranges"
- 150 ml red wine
- 2 tbsp sugar
- 1 bag mulled wine spices
- 2 tbsp rum
Zest {1} orange. Juice all the oranges. Bring {150} ml of the orange juice, the red wine and the sugar to a boil,
setting the remaining orange juice aside. Add the orange zest and the spices and let steep for 3 minutes.
Pass through a sieve, let cool and add rum.
-> mulled wine
-> remaining orange juice

- 200 g marzipan
- "orange juice"
- 2 tbsp rum
- 200 g dried apricots
- 100 g white chocolate
- 200 g chopped almonds
@ Remaining orange juice
Mix marzipan with {10} tbsp of orange juice and the rum until homogeneous. Finely dice apricots and chop chocolate.
Knead apricots, chocolate and almonds into the marzipan.
-> marzipan filling

@ sponge
@ marzipan filling 
@ mulled wine
Halve sponge horizontally. Soak bottom half with half of the mulled wine and spread half of the marzipan filling
on top. Set the other half of the sponge on top and press down firmly. Also soak with mulled wine and spread filling.
Refridgerate for at least one hour.

- 150 g dark chocolate
- 120 g cream
- 10 g butter
Melt chocolate, cream and butter and let cool down to room temperature. Spread on the cold cake.

- "chopped almonds (optional, for decoration)"
- "chocolate shavings (optional, for decoration)"
Optionally, decorate with chocolate shavings and almonds.